Price says she has been banned from entering the College of Arts and Sciences, and barred from discussing her case with students or colleagues.

Price said she is receiving support from groups like the American Association of University Professors, the American Sociological Association and other organizations.

On Wednesday morning, Price presented a petition with 364 signatures to the vice provost, demanding her immediate reinstatement.

Neither Price nor the school administrators commented on the petition or the professor's future at the university.

